                                <H5>Introduction</H5>All applications need to 
                                store some sort of configuration values out side 
                                the application; to avoid recompilation when 
                                changes have to be made like the database 
                                connection string or the mail server etc. 
                                Earlier such configuration values were stored in 
                                .ini file or as a registry entry. In .net 
                                configuration values are placed in configuration 
                                file.There are three types of configuration file 
                                machine, application and publisher configuration 
                                files. For now we will deal with application 
                                configuration. 
                                <H5>How to add config file to vs.net 
                                project?</H5>App.config file is automatically 
                                added to the project when VB.net project is 
                                opened in visual studio.net.If you are using 
                                C#.net it’‘s a bit different ,you got to 
                                manually add a text file from projects/add new 
                                item/select text file. After adding the text 
                                file to project and rename the file as 
                                App.config and add below XML sections. Database 
                                connection string can be included in the 
                                &lt;appSettings&gt; section of the app.config. 
                                <DIV class=Codewindow><PRE> 
  &lt;configuration &gt; 
      &lt;appSettings&gt; 
      &lt;!-- User application and configured property settings go here.--&gt; 
      &lt;!-- Connection string values --&gt; 
           &lt;add key="Provider" value="MSDAORA" &gt; 
	   &lt;add key="DataSource" value="DBTest" &gt; 
	   &lt;add key="UserID" value="Lavanya" &gt; 
	   &lt;add key="Password" value="Password" &gt; 
	   &lt;add key="MailServer" value="EXCH.XYZ.COM" &gt; 
      &lt;/appSettings&gt; 
  &lt;/configuration&gt; 
</PRE></DIV>
                                <H5>Name Spaces</H5>Use the following nameapaces 
                                to read the key value pairs 
                                <DIV class=Codewindow><PRE>System.Collections.Specialized.NameValueCollection 
System.Configuration.ConfigurationSettings
</PRE></DIV>The values of the configuration file 
                                can be retrieved by using the AppSettings method 
                                of System.Configuration.ConfigurationSettings 
                                object. This method returns a key and value 
                                collection of the in the <APPSETTING>section of 
                                app.config. 
                                <DIV class=Codewindow><PRE>VB.NET 
------
 Dim colNameVal As 
 System.Collections.Specialized.NameValueCollection 
 colNameVal = System.Configuration.ConfigurationSettings.AppSettings 
 Dim str As String 
 For Each str In colNameVal.AllKeys 
  Debug.WriteLine(colNameVal.Get(str)) 
 Next 
End 
Sub 

C#. NET
-------- 
 System.Collections.Specialized.NameValueCollection colNameVal; 
 colNameVal = System.Configuration.ConfigurationSettings.AppSettings; 
 foreach(string str in colNameVal.AllKeys) 
	{ 
	Debug.WriteLine(colNameVal.Get(str)); 
	} 
</PRE></DIV><BR>
                                <H5>Note:</H5>· XML case sensitive and the 
                                section should be in the same case as shown in 
                                the article. <BR>· Get method return returns a 
                                string so got to convert to the respective data 
                                type.<BR>· Modifications to the configuration 
                                file will not be reflected in the application 
                                immediately but only on the next restart of the 
                                application. 
